1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:02,070
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,780
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:07,150 --> 00:00:08,980
Yes. Stay away from balls.

4
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:12,250
What is it? What's wrong?

5
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:13,250
(Episode 16)

6
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:14,290
Did you have a nightmare?

7
00:00:15,450 --> 00:00:19,990
Honey, I told you the shaman said
to stay away from round balls.

8
00:00:20,390 --> 00:00:22,660
Yes, like a basketball
or a golf ball...

9
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:24,460
A golf ball.

10
00:00:25,030 --> 00:00:28,370
The fact that I dreamt about it
means today must be the day.

11
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:30,200
A golf ball.

12
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,210
Let's be careful today, honey.
You know there's always a hitch.

13
00:00:34,570 --> 00:00:37,580
Right. And today's the day we meet
our future rich daughter-in-law.

14
00:00:37,980 --> 00:00:39,080
Then we absolutely
can't let that happen.

15
00:00:44,350 --> 00:00:45,450
Come on.

16
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:50,050
Hey, that's enough.
Let's just stop already.

17
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,920
Hang on, just a little more.

18
00:00:53,730 --> 00:00:54,730
Good grief.

19
00:00:55,130 --> 00:00:58,230
- All this fuss.
- Tell me about it.

20
00:00:58,430 --> 00:01:00,900
Hey, relax a little.

21
00:01:01,130 --> 00:01:03,740
I'm going to make you look
ridiculously young today.

22
00:01:03,940 --> 00:01:04,940
No, don't.

23
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,710
Hey, be gentle!
That hurts. I'm done.

24
00:01:07,710 --> 00:01:10,110
- Oh, please. Who cares if it hurts?
- Seriously.

25
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:13,240
What matters is looking good
for your wife's fans.

26
00:01:13,450 --> 00:01:16,780
- I swear...
- Grandma, Dad's handsome, right?

27
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:19,180
Of course. Look who his mother is.

28
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:22,820
- Right?
- Yes, I guess he is handsome.

29
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,690
Hey. What's wrong
with being good-looking?

30
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:27,190
It's his behavior
that's the problem.

31
00:01:28,030 --> 00:01:31,100
Mom, how long are you going to
hold this against me? Come on.

32
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:34,070
You have to do well today
and get in your wife's good graces.

33
00:01:34,270 --> 00:01:35,970
Then, Mom will finally forgive you.

34
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:38,370
Exactly. Dae Han nailed it.

35
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:40,970
- Okay, almost done.
- Okay.

36
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:49,080
Seong Mi is almost done.
Why are you all taking so long?

37
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:50,850
Do you want to get an earful
for being late again?

38
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:53,180
I know,
he really should be leaving now.

39
00:01:53,690 --> 00:01:55,120
Hey, Woo Jae, are you almost done?

40
00:01:55,690 --> 00:01:59,660
Okay, all done! Ta-da!

41
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:03,060
- Oh, my.
- So? What do you think?

42
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:06,160
- What do you think, Mom?
- You look sharp, Gong Jeong Han.

43
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:07,530
Doesn't he look more like my brother
than my dad?

44
00:02:08,070 --> 00:02:09,300
My big brother, Jeong Han.

45
00:02:09,930 --> 00:02:11,540
You silly kid.

46
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,540
But you'll be playing golf today.
Can you really go dressed like that?

47
00:02:14,610 --> 00:02:16,070
Shouldn't you be dressed up a bit?

48
00:02:16,270 --> 00:02:18,510
They said the wardrobe's all set,
so he can just go in casual clothes.

49
00:02:19,140 --> 00:02:22,810
All right.
Let's go win over Dr. Han Seong Mi.

50
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:23,920
Hold on.

51
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:27,120
You're forgetting the final touch.
Here, these sunglasses.

52
00:02:27,490 --> 00:02:29,420
Oh, sunglasses.

53
00:02:29,420 --> 00:02:31,420
- Yes.
- Oh, my.

54
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:32,760
- Nice.
- Yes.

55
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,060
How do I look?

56
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:37,530
Are you Tom Cruise?

57
00:02:37,830 --> 00:02:39,360
Yes, I'm Tom.

58
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:44,740
- Mom's going to love this.
- Hey, should I take the bike?

59
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,470
Are you serious?

60
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:00,620
Okay, this way.

61
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,760
Here.

62
00:03:06,860 --> 00:03:07,860
Take them off.

63
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:10,160
What?

64
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:15,700
No wonder I couldn't really see.
Yes, I should take them off.

65
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:21,810
Everything has a price.

66
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:25,310
You look like Tom Cruise today,
honey.

67
00:03:27,550 --> 00:03:31,220
And you, Se Ri, really look the part
of a woman with powerful in-laws.

68
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,350
To think we're becoming
like royalty.

69
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,050
It feels like a dream.

70
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:40,990
But compared to Taehan Group...

71
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:42,860
Aren't they a bit out of our league?

72
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:46,400
Now, I'm worried
about the nomination.

73
00:03:48,170 --> 00:03:49,970
You should get in touch
with Councilor Hwang's people.

74
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:54,140
Becoming in-laws with Taehan Group
has to score us some points, right?

75
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:57,740
Honey, please.
This is Cha Se Ri you're talking to.

76
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,910
You think I haven't already?

77
00:03:59,510 --> 00:04:01,780
That's my Cha Se Ri,
always one step ahead.

78
00:04:02,650 --> 00:04:04,950
Apparently,
he kept asking if it was true...

79
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:06,720
that we're becoming in-laws
with the Taehan Group.

80
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:09,920
And when he heard about
"Human Theater,"

81
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:13,190
he said it would help the district.
He was absolutely thrilled.

82
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:14,930
He was?

83
00:04:16,460 --> 00:04:19,930
Oh, boy.
Jeong Han hasn't even agreed yet.

84
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,870
This is driving me nuts.
That sneaky jerk.

85
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:31,410
Honey,
have you been practicing at all?

86
00:04:31,780 --> 00:04:34,410
Of course.
I've been practicing really hard.

87
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:37,850
Just try to behave today,
and don't make a scene.

88
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:43,720
I won't embarrass you, Han Seong Mi.
So please, just have a little faith.

89
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:47,090
It's hard to trust you
when I've been burned so many times.

90
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:51,430
Okay, fine.
I'm a serial promise-breaker.

91
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:56,200
Listen.
Did you know Ju Ah has a boyfriend?

92
00:04:57,670 --> 00:04:58,940
Ju Ah has a boyfriend?

93
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:03,310
- It's a secret, so don't let on.
- Okay, got it.

94
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:07,980
But you just said it was a secret.
So why are you telling me?

95
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:12,120
Because we're going to
meet him there today.

96
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:14,420
Is it someone from work?

97
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,920
Don't tell me it's Bucket's son.

98
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,090
Absolutely not.

99
00:05:21,930 --> 00:05:24,430
I'll tell you who it is.
I want you to size him up.

100
00:05:25,130 --> 00:05:26,860
He's one of Ju Ah's
close work friends.

101
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,570
His name is Jun Hyeok.

102
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:29,870
Jun Hyeok?

103
00:05:30,470 --> 00:05:32,240
Okay, got it.

104
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,540
I'll get a good look
and see what kind of guy he is.

105
00:05:34,910 --> 00:05:35,940
Jun Hyeok.

106
00:05:56,590 --> 00:05:58,560
Dr. Han and her husband are here.

107
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:00,500
Ms. Gong, Mr. Park.

108
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:02,900
Let's go greet them
on behalf of the Design Team.

109
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:05,070
- Okay.
- Right.

110
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:15,150
I'm so nervous
now that your father's coming.

111
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:18,280
Just relax.

112
00:06:19,180 --> 00:06:21,990
Imagine my parents were coming.
Think you'd be able to relax?

113
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,220
I feel sick just thinking about it.

114
00:06:26,990 --> 00:06:28,130
Hello, everyone.

115
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,030
What the...

116
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:52,380
(One-Point Lesson
With Dr. Han Seong Mi)

117
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:53,580
Honey, you look elegant today.

118
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,190
Your makeup looks nice.

119
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:59,220
- Hello, Dr. Han.
- I'm such a big fan.

120
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:01,090
- Thank you.
- Yes, thank you very much.

121
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:04,760
Hey.

122
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,200
Did you learn to play golf
just to come here?

123
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:10,940
So what if I did?
Why didn't you say you were coming?

124
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,070
I didn't know I was.

125
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:15,740
I got a last-minute invitation
yesterday.

126
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:19,240
The Vice President
of Taehan Group...

127
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,850
is set to marry our son, Hyun Bin.

128
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:23,250
What?

129
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:27,490
I was under the impression
that wasn't their relationship.

130
00:07:27,790 --> 00:07:29,990
Come on. What do you mean?

131
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:34,590
My gosh.
Dr. Han, you sound a little jealous.

132
00:07:34,990 --> 00:07:36,930
Jealous? Me?

133
00:07:37,230 --> 00:07:41,100
Considering your daughter is
well past marrying age,

134
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,930
I can see why
you might be a little jealous.

135
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:48,070
But don't you worry.
There's a lid for every pot.

136
00:07:48,210 --> 00:07:49,970
I'm sure she'll find someone nice
soon enough, right?

137
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:54,010
I'm always struck by
your rather unique train of thought.

138
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:58,450
My, what odd things you worry about.
Anyway, our daughter...

139
00:07:58,650 --> 00:08:03,290
- already has a boyfriend.
- Does she, really?

140
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:04,890
Absolutely.

141
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:08,360
Oh, my. That's wonderful news.

142
00:08:09,230 --> 00:08:10,660
To be perfectly honest,

143
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:13,930
I was a little worried
she might end up with my Hyun Bin.

144
00:08:14,070 --> 00:08:17,440
There's zero chance of that,
so you can rest assured.

145
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,170
Right, of course.

146
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:25,480
What do you think you're doing?
Why would you invite my parents...

147
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:27,080
without even telling me first?

148
00:08:27,380 --> 00:08:30,550
To help your families reconcile,
announce your relationship,

149
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:32,980
- and get their blessing to marry.
- What did you just say?

150
00:08:33,990 --> 00:08:36,290
- Did you think I wouldn't find out?
- Find out about what?

151
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:38,220
- I know everything.
- "Everything" about what?

152
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:41,060
That Pacu Nacho and Ms. Gong
are dating.

153
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:44,400
And that Dr. Han Seong Mi
is Ms. Gong's mother.

154
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,100
Wait, how do you know that?

155
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:54,110
But why did the VP invite
Director Yang's parents...

156
00:08:54,110 --> 00:08:55,810
without telling him?

157
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,410
About that...

158
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:03,310
Well, I told her...

159
00:09:03,450 --> 00:09:07,150
the secret that Dr. Han is your mom.

160
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:09,250
What? Are you out of your mind?

161
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:11,690
I told you that was a secret,
didn't I?

162
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:14,390
Okay, you did. I'm sorry, my friend.

163
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:17,760
Friend? Do friends tell
each other's secrets?

164
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:21,830
Hey. What about you?
Do you even think of me as a friend?

165
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:25,340
The nerve of you!
How dare you turn this on me?

166
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:28,210
You hid the fact that
you're dating Director Yang from me!

167
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:31,640
Who told you that? Who?
We're not dating, okay?

168
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,240
Are you sure about that?

169
00:09:33,580 --> 00:09:37,250
- I'm positive.
- Look me in the eye and say it.

170
00:09:38,650 --> 00:09:41,690
We are not dating, Ms. Hwangbo.

171
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:44,060
See? She said we're not.

172
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:46,590
How can you not be dating?
You two kissed.

173
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:57,540
That's right. I told her.
For our Fashion Division!

174
00:09:57,770 --> 00:09:59,970
And how exactly is this
for the Fashion Division?

175
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:03,440
Because Pacu Nacho is indispensable
to our Fashion Division.

176
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:07,040
We can't just let you leave
in a year.

177
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:10,850
To help with your biggest problem,
your parents being like enemies,

178
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:15,020
we invited them here today
to try to resolve the situation.

179
00:10:15,290 --> 00:10:16,290
No.

180
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:19,590
We're not even dating,
but you made our feuding parents...

181
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,730
sit face-to-face like that,
Ms. Hwangbo.

182
00:10:24,330 --> 00:10:25,530
That can't be right.

183
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,650
You should have some too, Dr. Han.

184
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:52,190
Here. Wow, this looks delicious.

185
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:54,230
This is good!

186
00:10:54,860 --> 00:10:57,560
I take it that
you two haven't made up yet?

187
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,560
- Excuse me?
- What?

188
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:01,570
I heard you almost got divorced
because...

189
00:11:01,570 --> 00:11:03,100
he kept the moving issue from you.

190
00:11:08,970 --> 00:11:09,970
Hey.

191
00:11:10,410 --> 00:11:13,710
You'll just tell anyone anything,
won't you?

192
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:18,050
We decided to keep no more secrets
from each other.

193
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,920
It's all so fascinating, Doctor.

194
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:25,660
First, your "prescribing love" act,
you do these modeling gigs,

195
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:28,160
and you even attend events together
as a couple,

196
00:11:28,490 --> 00:11:31,100
but in reality,
your marriage is on the rocks.

197
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:37,100
- It's so amusing. So hypocritical.
- You find this amusing, do you?

198
00:11:41,670 --> 00:11:42,670
Here they come.

199
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:48,410
You'd better handle this well.
If you bring us up,

200
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:52,350
our parents could start a war,
so don't slip up. Got it?

201
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:54,820
- I said I get it.
- Why, you...

202
00:11:55,420 --> 00:11:59,090
Oh, my goodness.
The two of them look great together.

203
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:05,500
- We're honored to have you here.
- Yes.

204
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:09,470
No, we should be thanking you
for the invitation. Actually...

205
00:12:09,530 --> 00:12:11,940
Weren't we told to come early
for the event?

206
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:15,070
What is this gathering all about?

207
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:17,370
Oh, it's...

208
00:12:18,540 --> 00:12:19,580
Vice President.

209
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:23,680
Dr. Han's family
and Director Yang's family...

210
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:25,950
I hear you go way back.

211
00:12:26,420 --> 00:12:29,120
Dr. Han, you're a model
for our company, Taehan,

212
00:12:29,190 --> 00:12:32,920
and Director Yang handles
your work with the brand, you know.

213
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:34,290
However,

214
00:12:34,690 --> 00:12:38,200
if your family and his parents
aren't on good terms,

215
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:41,330
that must make it very difficult
for Director Yang to do his job.

216
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,600
What is she talking about?

217
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,270
Is that seriously your excuse?

218
00:12:48,610 --> 00:12:49,610
Oh, my.

219
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:54,380
Our VP is so considerate.
That's right.

220
00:12:54,450 --> 00:12:58,080
If our families are on bad terms,
it would be hard on Director Yang.

221
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:00,820
Does
my exclusive modeling contract...

222
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:05,460
say I have to be friendly
with Director Yang's parents?

223
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:08,290
No. There was no such clause.

224
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:12,060
Since we're almost out of time,
shall we go to the fitting?

225
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,130
- You get up, too.
- What? Oh, okay.

226
00:13:14,270 --> 00:13:15,570
Right this way, then.

227
00:13:19,970 --> 00:13:24,210
Who even got her that contract?
She's so arrogant.

228
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:28,650
I'm afraid I may have misjudged
the situation.

229
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:30,080
Don't worry about it.

230
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:32,820
I do appreciate the sentiment,
but...

231
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:35,820
it's going to take more than this
for us to make up.

232
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:40,560
But still, for you to go
to all this trouble for Hyun Bin,

233
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:44,860
- we're so grateful, Vice President.
- Not at all. I'm the grateful one.

234
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:49,330
Director Yang has been a vital part
of my life since we studied abroad.

235
00:13:49,330 --> 00:13:50,330
My gosh.

236
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,540
My, did you hear that, honey?

237
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:56,170
Shall we head to the fitting?
Father, Mother.

238
00:13:58,140 --> 00:14:00,410
- "Father."
- "Father, Mother."

239
00:14:11,990 --> 00:14:15,190
So many people are watching.
Why risk a secret meeting?

240
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:18,260
You aren't mad I denied
we're dating, are you?

241
00:14:18,330 --> 00:14:21,700
Of course not. We agreed to deny it,
so what's the big deal?

242
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:23,670
Besides, if we get caught now,

243
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:27,100
who knows
what the VP will pull next?

244
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:31,610
- Right. We have to keep denying it.
- Right.

245
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:35,050
Well,
my parents must've surprised you.

246
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:37,450
Sorry, I should have warned you.

247
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:42,820
Since they're here, I want to make
a good impression. Any tips?

248
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:47,120
Well... My stepmom is
a former beauty queen,

249
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,830
so she loves compliments
about her looks.

250
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:53,360
Compliment her looks. Okay. Got it.

251
00:14:53,930 --> 00:14:55,330
- I'm going in.
- Okay.

252
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:59,000
Just relax. Be yourself.

253
00:15:01,310 --> 00:15:02,340
Relax.

254
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:11,480
That vibrant color
looks amazing on you.

255
00:15:12,850 --> 00:15:13,980
You think so?

256
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:20,560
Excuse me, but your name isn't here.
May I ask who you are?

257
00:15:22,430 --> 00:15:25,430
I'm Director Yang Hyun Bin's mother.

258
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:29,300
My gosh! Really? No way.

259
00:15:29,570 --> 00:15:31,140
You look way too young.

260
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,340
Thank you for the compliment.

261
00:15:35,770 --> 00:15:39,610
You're tall with such long limbs,
so the fit is perfect on you.

262
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,450
You think so?

263
00:15:41,850 --> 00:15:44,150
I think it makes me
look a bit puffy.

264
00:15:44,420 --> 00:15:47,450
Don't you have something
that's more cinched at the waist?

265
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:52,390
But if it's too tight, it'll be
uncomfortable when you're playing.

266
00:15:52,460 --> 00:15:56,990
Especially for your swing,
you need this much room to move.

267
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:02,730
I'm the type of person
who values looking pretty more.

268
00:16:03,030 --> 00:16:04,840
A little discomfort is a price
I'm willing to pay.

269
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:07,670
Come on. Get it altered for me.

270
00:16:08,340 --> 00:16:11,680
It's a sample
that has to be returned,

271
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:13,480
so we can't make any alterations.

272
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:19,350
I can use pins to cinch the waist
and accentuate the line for you.

273
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:25,660
- Like this...
- So here? About this much?

274
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:27,060
- Yes.
- Got it.

275
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:37,130
- It's a bit slippery. One second.
- Give it to me. I'll do it myself.

276
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:39,500
- No, I can...
- It's fine.

277
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,440
Go on and tend to your mother.

278
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,240
Excuse me?

279
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:47,380
What are you staring at?
I said go check on Dr. Han Seong Mi.

280
00:16:49,650 --> 00:16:52,220
Wait, Dr. Han Seong Mi
is Ms. Gong's mother?

281
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:56,490
What, was that supposed
to be a secret?

282
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:01,730
- I guess I was the last to know!
- No, it's just that...

283
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:05,230
Ouch, what do you think
you're doing?

284
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:08,230
My gosh, I'm so sorry.

285
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:11,340
Ouch, it stings.
I'm bleeding... Wait, did you...

286
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,740
- That really hurts!
- Oh, no.

287
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:15,910
My gosh. Did you do that on purpose?

288
00:17:15,910 --> 00:17:18,210
- No, I swear...
- Gosh, it really hurts.

289
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,310
For goodness' sake.

290
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:26,180
Are you all right?

291
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:29,850
The prick itself is nothing.

292
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:31,590
But it hurt my feelings.

293
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:34,220
I didn't mean to reveal her secret,

294
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:35,890
but to just stab someone over it
on purpose?

295
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:39,560
Stab you on purpose?
Ms. Gong would never do that.

296
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:41,430
What? Don't be ridiculous.

297
00:17:41,930 --> 00:17:43,570
Maybe this is
her way of getting revenge,

298
00:17:43,570 --> 00:17:45,100
because
Se Ri hit her mom in the past.

299
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,600
My goodness. That could be it.

300
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:49,440
Doing that to our pretty Se Ri.

301
00:17:52,140 --> 00:17:53,840
Why did you wash your hair
at this hour, Uncle?

302
00:17:53,910 --> 00:17:57,610
- What? Want to take a sniff?
- What? Gosh, no.

303
00:17:58,350 --> 00:18:01,120
Hey, don't use the shampoo
in the bathroom. It's just for me.

304
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:03,220
Whatever you say.

305
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:05,760
- I'm off to my part-time job.
- Wait, hold on.

306
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:08,460
What are you going to get your uncle
with your first paycheck?

307
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:10,830
Gosh, seriously.
Why would I buy you anything...

308
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:18,370
- Jack squat.
- Gosh, then forget it. Go.

309
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:20,270
Unbelievable.

310
00:18:25,340 --> 00:18:26,640
I love this smell.

311
00:18:27,780 --> 00:18:30,080
It smells so nice. What?

312
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:32,750
Oh, my heart...

313
00:18:34,690 --> 00:18:36,150
Even this pounding in my chest...

314
00:18:37,390 --> 00:18:38,920
is something
I'm getting used to now.

315
00:18:50,870 --> 00:18:53,970
Gosh, what now?
Why is he calling me?

316
00:18:58,740 --> 00:19:00,610
Yes? What's up?

317
00:19:02,180 --> 00:19:03,710
Hey, Dong Suk. You know what?

318
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,850
No matter
how much I think about it...

319
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:08,750
Think about what?

320
00:19:09,820 --> 00:19:11,690
I think I'm going to be rich
thanks to you.

321
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:14,220
- Rich?
- Yes.

322
00:19:15,190 --> 00:19:16,260
Rich with a full head of hair.

323
00:19:16,930 --> 00:19:18,430
So you got the shampoo?

324
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,530
You called me just for that?

325
00:19:21,630 --> 00:19:26,340
No, that's not why I called.
It's about what you said before.

326
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:28,840
What did I say?

327
00:19:29,510 --> 00:19:31,410
You asked me to tag along
to help you look for a store space.

328
00:19:32,210 --> 00:19:34,810
Oh, that.
It's fine. Don't worry about it.

329
00:19:35,710 --> 00:19:37,680
Come on, let's just go together.

330
00:19:38,380 --> 00:19:40,750
Market analysis
is totally my specialty.

331
00:19:41,650 --> 00:19:42,850
But...

332
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:46,820
it'd look a little weird
if we're seen together.

333
00:19:47,990 --> 00:19:50,930
What do you mean "seen together?"
We'd just be out together.

334
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:56,270
I worry people in the neighborhood
will see us and get the wrong idea.

335
00:19:56,770 --> 00:20:00,870
What's wrong? I'm an old friend
from the neighborhood helping out.

336
00:20:02,770 --> 00:20:05,440
Okay, fine. I'll call you
when I'm ready to go look.

337
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:09,050
You scared me!

338
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:10,580
Oh, my.

339
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:13,750
There's no ink to dry
on your divorce papers...

340
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:15,890
since you haven't even
signed them yet,

341
00:20:15,890 --> 00:20:17,620
and you're already seeing some guy!

342
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:20,060
Aren't you something else?

343
00:20:20,260 --> 00:20:22,730
What? I'm not seeing anyone!
Keep your voice down!

344
00:20:23,230 --> 00:20:26,530
"It'd look a little weird
if we're seen together."

345
00:20:26,730 --> 00:20:29,770
"Gosh, the neighbors
will get the wrong idea."

346
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:32,370
You said that. Who's this guy
from the neighborhood?

347
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:36,770
Shut it! Anyway,
about that influencer thing...

348
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:39,110
You said you needed money
for equipment, right?

349
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:41,650
Want me to give you a little tip?

350
00:20:42,150 --> 00:20:44,780
Nice try changing the subject.
What is it? What's the tip?

351
00:20:45,220 --> 00:20:50,120
If you need cash, don't ask your dad
or my dad. Go after your stepmom.

352
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:54,420
I tried that. It doesn't work
with my stepmom. She won't listen.

353
00:20:54,490 --> 00:20:59,100
No, don't just nag her for money.
You have to be nice to her.

354
00:20:59,230 --> 00:21:00,860
I am being nice to her.

355
00:21:01,230 --> 00:21:04,800
You need to make sure
your dad and my dad...

356
00:21:04,940 --> 00:21:06,240
see you being nice to her.

357
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:12,340
That's actually a pretty good idea.
If it works, I'll give you a cut.

358
00:21:12,910 --> 00:21:13,910
Whatever.

359
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:17,380
Oh, I wonder if she's met that rich
future daughter-in-law yet.

360
00:21:17,380 --> 00:21:19,220
What? That's not what's going on.

361
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:22,490
- You're barking up the wrong tree.
- I'll just ask her.

362
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:29,760
Of course.
I met our future daughter-in-law.

363
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,530
And she looks
so much younger than her age.

364
00:21:33,930 --> 00:21:37,400
And you won't believe how incredibly
good she is to our Hyun Bin.

365
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:41,510
I can't believe it.
Isn't it just amazing?

366
00:21:41,610 --> 00:21:43,910
Taehan Group's only daughter
is going to be my daughter-in-law.

367
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:46,040
Oh, my gosh. This is so exciting.

368
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:55,750
My gosh...

369
00:21:58,190 --> 00:22:00,690
Seriously. Why do you keep
saying things people misinterpret?

370
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:02,990
Dr. Han already got the wrong idea
about you last time.

371
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:05,130
Did I come all this way just to get
a lecture from you, Mr. Park?

372
00:22:05,530 --> 00:22:07,160
I need you to come up with a plan.

373
00:22:07,230 --> 00:22:08,800
What plan could there possibly be?

374
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:11,970
You need to sort this out quickly
before Director Yang finds out.

375
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:13,870
- Me?
- You want me to do it?

376
00:22:14,540 --> 00:22:16,610
Do it. That's an order
from the Vice President.

377
00:22:17,540 --> 00:22:19,340
No way. Hurry up and go.

378
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:24,510
Come on. Just go already!

379
00:22:43,770 --> 00:22:46,440
I have absolutely no intention
of marrying Director Yang Hyun Bin.

380
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:51,010
Director Yang and I have been close
since our school days,

381
00:22:51,510 --> 00:22:54,180
but I needed to make it clear that
our relationship isn't romantic.

382
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:56,450
With the purest of intentions,

383
00:22:57,310 --> 00:23:00,620
I hoped you'd become good friends
with Dr. Han and her husband.

384
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:09,830
Well then, I hope
you all have a wonderful time.

385
00:23:17,470 --> 00:23:19,040
They were totally
getting ahead of themselves...

386
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:25,640
This event...

387
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:29,850
is to sponsor a mental health fund
in our customers' names,

388
00:23:30,310 --> 00:23:33,480
marking the first step
of FG's new charity project,

389
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:38,520
and is also a preview of
our new Hot Summer Season line.

390
00:23:40,020 --> 00:23:44,060
And now, for today's special guest,

391
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:47,060
the new face of
our Hot Summer Season,

392
00:23:57,840 --> 00:23:59,310
and FG's main model!

393
00:23:59,540 --> 00:24:02,950
The woman who prescribes love,
bringing joy to Korean families.

394
00:24:03,510 --> 00:24:05,550
Please welcome Dr. Han Seong Mi!

395
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:15,730
- She's gorgeous.
- Wow, she's beautiful.

396
00:24:15,790 --> 00:24:19,400
And today, we have a special treat.
Dr. Han Seong Mi's partner,

397
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:22,230
Mr. Gong Jeong Han,
is also here with us.

398
00:24:22,630 --> 00:24:25,040
Oh, me too?

399
00:24:25,770 --> 00:24:26,770
Okay, all right.

400
00:24:28,170 --> 00:24:30,210
Yes. Hello, everyone. Hello!

401
00:24:30,210 --> 00:24:31,810
- So handsome!
- You're so handsome.

402
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:35,780
You're all so lovely and handsome.
Thank you. Thank you so much.

403
00:24:36,210 --> 00:24:38,420
So I guess
we were just the opening act.

404
00:24:40,220 --> 00:24:42,820
Honey, wipe that look off your face.
The cameras are on you.

405
00:24:53,230 --> 00:24:56,530
Now, we'll begin the demo lesson
with Dr. Han Seong Mi.

406
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:10,410
A light grip,
feet shoulder-width apart.

407
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:14,450
Align your club and shoulders
with the target. That's good.

408
00:25:15,850 --> 00:25:18,420
Takeaway, backswing, top.

409
00:25:22,830 --> 00:25:25,960
Nice shot, Dr. Han! Nice shot!

410
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,770
Great job! That was great!

411
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:36,710
You're way better than her.
Later, put her in her place. Got it?

412
00:25:36,810 --> 00:25:39,840
Of course. Leave it to me.
I'm Cha Se Ri, above Pak Se Ri.

413
00:25:41,310 --> 00:25:43,980
Let's head out
for some 1-on-1 coaching.

414
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:45,920
Not bad, right?

415
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:48,850
- Hey, he's a good instructor.
- Grip it longer...

416
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:50,950
- Like this? Yes.
- Put it in front of your left foot.

417
00:25:51,020 --> 00:25:52,890
- Yes, that's right.
- When you place it here...

418
00:25:52,890 --> 00:25:54,690
- You got this, right?
- Keep your back straight.

419
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:57,860
Is it a little tight in the armpits
when he swings?

420
00:25:58,860 --> 00:26:01,670
Exactly. So we should probably
widen the armholes.

421
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:06,670
- Back straight. Eyes on the ball.
- The hemline needs adjusting...

422
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:08,910
- Yes, that's right.
- Want to try it? Hold the position.

423
00:26:08,970 --> 00:26:10,770
- Yes.
- That's it.

424
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,580
- Do you want to give it a shot?
- Let me try. All right.

425
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:14,040
And swing.

426
00:26:17,580 --> 00:26:21,750
Great shot. Your release is solid,
and your impact is very stable.

427
00:26:22,290 --> 00:26:24,250
Thank you. Hey.

428
00:26:25,490 --> 00:26:28,630
Gosh, what a show-off.
Sit back down.

429
00:26:29,430 --> 00:26:30,430
Thanks.

430
00:26:30,790 --> 00:26:33,030
- Shall we take a practice swing?
- Yes.

431
00:26:33,100 --> 00:26:34,600
- Practice swing.
- You can count on me.

432
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,100
I'm Cha Se Ri,
better than Pak Se Ri.

433
00:26:45,910 --> 00:26:47,840
- Shall we take your address?
- Yes.

434
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:52,180
Good.

435
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,450
That's very good.

436
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:58,990
- Wow, your form is flawless.
- Is it?

437
00:26:59,060 --> 00:27:00,160
- Just relax.
- Time to show them what I got.

438
00:27:00,220 --> 00:27:01,990
Now, feel like you're throwing it
with your forearms.

439
00:27:02,790 --> 00:27:04,660
- Like I'm throwing it?
- Yes.

440
00:27:04,730 --> 00:27:06,430
- So, like I'm throwing it?
- Yes. Now...

441
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:07,500
Here, like this.

442
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,870
Hand. Oh, like this.

443
00:27:09,930 --> 00:27:13,370
Hey, you fool.
Feel it in your butt. Right, left.

444
00:27:14,170 --> 00:27:16,440
Hey, shut it! I know what I'm doing!

445
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,740
- So annoying.
- Whatever.

446
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:21,610
What? Darn it...

447
00:27:23,110 --> 00:27:24,110
I'll...

448
00:27:24,650 --> 00:27:27,920
Right, left. I will show him.

449
00:27:51,410 --> 00:27:52,740
Stay away from balls.

450
00:27:53,510 --> 00:27:54,710
Stay away from balls.

451
00:27:55,410 --> 00:27:56,410
The ball?

452
00:28:13,230 --> 00:28:14,300
No!

453
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:19,800
Oh, no!

454
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:27,580
Oh, no!

455
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:31,480
Honey! Se Ri!

456
00:28:34,450 --> 00:28:37,190
Call 911! Call an ambulance, quick!

457
00:28:38,220 --> 00:28:39,220
Se Ri, stay with me!

458
00:28:40,220 --> 00:28:43,530
Honey, what do we do?
Oh, no. This is crazy.

459
00:28:57,940 --> 00:28:59,410
There you all are.

460
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:01,640
Any word from the hospital?

461
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:04,780
Yes. Luckily,
they say it's nothing serious.

462
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:08,850
I'm so sorry, Ms. Hwangbo.

463
00:29:10,490 --> 00:29:14,090
What's done is done.
Let's just focus on damage control.

464
00:29:15,630 --> 00:29:16,630
Yes.

465
00:29:20,530 --> 00:29:21,600
Relax and lean back.

466
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:27,100
I feel so terrible.
I didn't ruin the event, did I?

467
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:30,840
Not at all. I heard everything
went off without a hitch.

468
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,140
It's my fault, honey.

469
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:36,780
I kept cursing at Jeong Han,
wishing he'd hit a terrible shot.

470
00:29:37,550 --> 00:29:41,120
How is that your fault?
The one who shanked the shot...

471
00:29:41,380 --> 00:29:43,450
and the person who pushed me
are the ones to blame.

472
00:29:43,850 --> 00:29:45,360
Gosh, I'll make them pay for this!

473
00:29:45,420 --> 00:29:48,390
Come on, it's not like anyone
did it on purpose, right?

474
00:29:48,460 --> 00:29:51,360
Accidents from mishits happen
on the range all the time.

475
00:29:52,260 --> 00:29:56,970
Honestly, I could see the pinprick
being an accident,

476
00:29:57,230 --> 00:30:00,740
but pushing me like that
feels pretty intentional.

477
00:30:01,340 --> 00:30:05,140
What?
It absolutely wasn't intentional.

478
00:30:05,210 --> 00:30:08,910
Please, no grudges. Just rest
so you can get better faster, okay?

479
00:30:14,820 --> 00:30:17,120
It's such a relief it wasn't worse.

480
00:30:17,420 --> 00:30:21,290
I know. If she'd been badly hurt,
she would have made a huge scene.

481
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:24,530
After practicing for so many days...
Goodness.

482
00:30:24,860 --> 00:30:26,060
How did that even happen?

483
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:29,200
Well, that jerk Bucket was behind me
making faces,

484
00:30:29,470 --> 00:30:31,500
and he kept messing with me.
It was so annoying.

485
00:30:31,570 --> 00:30:34,500
Good grief. He's always like that.

486
00:30:34,770 --> 00:30:37,140
Honestly, he needs to act his age.

487
00:30:37,810 --> 00:30:40,910
Dong Suk's okay, but her brother
is really something else.

488
00:30:44,410 --> 00:30:46,850
And Ju Ah? Is Ju Ah okay?

489
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:50,350
She was pretty shaken up,
but she's fine.

490
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:52,460
She said she'll come home
after wrapping up the event.

491
00:30:53,660 --> 00:30:55,730
The event wrapped up okay, right?

492
00:30:55,890 --> 00:30:59,100
Yes, thankfully.
We even finished the fan signing.

493
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:02,470
Yes. Oh, but Mom,
you should have seen Bucket today.

494
00:31:02,630 --> 00:31:05,340
He totally jumped the gun.

495
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:09,370
- What?
- Jumped the gun? What happened?

496
00:31:10,310 --> 00:31:11,910
Get this.

497
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:16,210
He thought his son and the VP,
the Chairman's daughter,

498
00:31:16,510 --> 00:31:19,120
were getting married or something.

499
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:22,650
And? Wait, they're not?

500
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:26,820
Hey, it was worse than that.
The Vice President...

501
00:31:26,890 --> 00:31:28,830
came right up to our family
and Bucket's...

502
00:31:29,230 --> 00:31:33,100
and said,
"I have absolutely no intention..."

503
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:35,160
"of marrying
Director Yang Hyun Bin!"

504
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,400
And then, she just bolted!

505
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:41,340
My, there must have been
some kind of misunderstanding, then.

506
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:45,680
It was beyond a misunderstanding.
We were mortified for them.

507
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:48,280
Man, you should've seen
the look on Bucket's face.

508
00:31:50,110 --> 00:31:53,480
I told you it was the wrong idea,
didn't I?

509
00:31:53,750 --> 00:31:56,220
How did everyone get that idea
in the first place?

510
00:31:56,290 --> 00:32:01,090
Hey, the VP called herself
and said it was a surprise.

511
00:32:01,460 --> 00:32:04,590
We heard you only came back to Korea
because she asked you to.

512
00:32:04,690 --> 00:32:06,660
We assumed that's why
you blew off the blind date...

513
00:32:06,660 --> 00:32:08,060
with Councilor Hwang's daughter.

514
00:32:08,130 --> 00:32:11,130
No, that's not it.
She's just a close friend.

515
00:32:12,170 --> 00:32:14,500
Your stepmother must be
incredibly disappointed.

516
00:32:15,310 --> 00:32:18,240
Grandfather is
really disappointed, too.

517
00:32:19,110 --> 00:32:20,110
Who, me?

518
00:32:21,540 --> 00:32:24,080
What did they say at the hospital?
Are they sure it's nothing serious?

519
00:32:24,450 --> 00:32:27,880
Yes. They took some X-rays.
No fractures, just a sprain.

520
00:32:28,950 --> 00:32:33,220
Use a cold compress for the fever.
Check on her tonight. It may throb.

521
00:32:33,390 --> 00:32:36,590
- Okay.
- But are there any videos?

522
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:39,560
A video of her falling. I'm curious.

523
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,730
You don't think someone
will post that online, do you?

524
00:32:42,730 --> 00:32:45,500
Why would they? They only filmed
their own lessons, not others.

525
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:48,140
They promised
to keep all the videos private,

526
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:49,770
and I've already handled
the reporters.

527
00:32:54,540 --> 00:32:56,050
Your son looks great
in that picture, doesn't he?

528
00:32:56,910 --> 00:32:58,080
My gosh.

529
00:32:59,050 --> 00:33:02,420
My son's success is
all thanks to his amazing wife.

530
00:33:03,690 --> 00:33:07,290
He did well
aside from that one bad shot today.

531
00:33:08,490 --> 00:33:09,530
So?

532
00:33:09,930 --> 00:33:12,560
Have you forgiven Jeong Han now?

533
00:33:13,630 --> 00:33:15,470
There's nothing to forgive.

534
00:33:16,300 --> 00:33:17,900
It is what it is.

535
00:33:18,600 --> 00:33:21,300
Right. That's a good way
to think about it.

536
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:25,510
That reminds me. Ju Ah.
Did you meet her boyfriend?

537
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:30,510
Ju Ah's father invited him over,
and he said he'd come.

538
00:33:30,650 --> 00:33:33,750
Really? Let me think.

539
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:35,850
What should we cook for him?

540
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:41,390
You're already planning the menu?
Ju Ah doesn't even know we know.

541
00:33:44,590 --> 00:33:48,430
Ju Ah must be so upset today.
I hope he's taking good care of her.

542
00:33:49,100 --> 00:33:50,100
I'm sure.

543
00:33:50,630 --> 00:33:53,300
That must be why she's out so late.

544
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:07,380
Your stepmom thinks
it was deliberate, doesn't she?

545
00:34:07,780 --> 00:34:10,890
No. Why would she think that?

546
00:34:11,390 --> 00:34:14,020
My stepmom isn't like that.
You've got it all wrong.

547
00:34:14,620 --> 00:34:17,460
She said if you hadn't caught it,
it would've hit her in the face.

548
00:34:17,530 --> 00:34:18,860
She was actually saying
how thankful she was.

549
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:22,200
You're such a bad liar.

550
00:34:22,770 --> 00:34:25,540
No, I'm not lying.

551
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:27,670
Whatever.

552
00:34:33,340 --> 00:34:37,080
Your mom even saw my bare chest.

553
00:34:40,550 --> 00:34:41,550
Hyun Bin.

554
00:34:43,220 --> 00:34:45,820
Why do you sound so serious
when you say my name?

555
00:34:46,860 --> 00:34:49,390
What if we just date for one year?

556
00:34:49,690 --> 00:34:52,860
- Until you return to Argentina.
- No, wait.

557
00:34:53,500 --> 00:34:56,930
How can you say
something so horrible?

558
00:34:57,700 --> 00:35:01,400
That's my point. I don't think
I could ever break up with you.

559
00:35:02,210 --> 00:35:03,440
What am I supposed to do?

560
00:35:04,070 --> 00:35:06,680
Promise you'll never say that again,
no matter how upset you get.

561
00:35:07,510 --> 00:35:08,510
Okay.

562
00:35:10,680 --> 00:35:11,750
By the way,

563
00:35:12,150 --> 00:35:15,280
how did you catch the ball
so quickly?

564
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:16,720
You have amazing reflexes.

565
00:35:17,350 --> 00:35:19,490
The moment
the ball came flying at me,

566
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:23,730
- a scene flashed before my eyes.
- What scene?

567
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:28,230
A scene where my dad's ball
hits your stepmom.

568
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:39,940
- Oh, no!
- Honey! Se Ri!

569
00:35:40,740 --> 00:35:41,940
You scumbag!

570
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:44,850
- You hurt my wife on purpose!
- And then,

571
00:35:45,110 --> 00:35:47,380
a scene of your father getting angry
and starting to fight my dad.

572
00:35:47,450 --> 00:35:49,020
A full-on fistfight with my dad.

573
00:35:49,450 --> 00:35:50,450
You scumbag!

574
00:35:52,420 --> 00:35:54,190
Oh, no. This is crazy!

575
00:35:56,190 --> 00:36:00,200
And then, I saw people filming it,
the event turning into chaos,

576
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:03,900
and the headlines flashing,
"Brawl Breaks Out at FG Event."

577
00:36:05,430 --> 00:36:09,870
"Dr. Han Seong Mi's Husband
Brawls With FG Director's Father."

578
00:36:10,210 --> 00:36:11,210
Yes.

579
00:36:11,670 --> 00:36:14,940
That's why I jumped in
without a second thought.

580
00:36:16,310 --> 00:36:17,550
You did the right thing.

581
00:36:17,610 --> 00:36:20,380
Thanks to you, it didn't blow up,
and nobody got hurt.

582
00:36:21,120 --> 00:36:23,790
You're so clueless.
You think that's the only problem?

583
00:36:24,290 --> 00:36:28,290
- You're so clueless.
- What? What am I clueless about?

584
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:32,130
I'm talking about your mother.
She fell right in front of my mom.

585
00:36:32,300 --> 00:36:34,700
Can you imagine how upset
and humiliated she must be?

586
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:39,340
- You think so?
- Of course. My mom loved it.

587
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:40,800
She's probably still smiling
in her sleep.

588
00:36:41,100 --> 00:36:44,270
Come on.
Would Dr. Han really do that?

589
00:37:17,640 --> 00:37:21,740
I told you. I can't today.
I have some shopping to do.

590
00:37:21,810 --> 00:37:24,680
Honestly. Okay, So Hye.
I'll see you tomorrow.

591
00:37:26,250 --> 00:37:27,250
Off to your part-time job?

592
00:37:28,380 --> 00:37:30,850
You're not actually dating Hyun Bin,
are you?

593
00:37:31,020 --> 00:37:32,020
No. Why?

594
00:37:32,990 --> 00:37:35,190
I heard you pushed his mom
yesterday.

595
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:37,390
It's not like I did it on purpose.

596
00:37:38,090 --> 00:37:39,830
When did I say
you did it on purpose?

597
00:37:40,130 --> 00:37:42,830
Besides, on purpose or not,
you still pushed her.

598
00:37:43,870 --> 00:37:44,870
I guess so.

599
00:37:46,940 --> 00:37:48,570
You two will never get together.

600
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,440
Yes. Get lost.

601
00:37:50,710 --> 00:37:51,810
No, I don't want to.

602
00:37:52,410 --> 00:37:55,310
Gong Woo Jae, what will you buy me
with your first paycheck?

603
00:37:55,950 --> 00:37:57,080
You can't squeeze blood
from a stone.

604
00:37:57,910 --> 00:37:59,280
That kid, I swear.

605
00:38:00,220 --> 00:38:01,220
Good grief.

606
00:38:01,980 --> 00:38:03,250
Seriously.

607
00:38:10,030 --> 00:38:12,130
Here, open wide.

608
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:19,240
What's gotten into you?

609
00:38:20,570 --> 00:38:23,140
She made all this food and cooked
porridge for our stepmom too.

610
00:38:23,740 --> 00:38:26,080
Not just any porridge.
It's mushroom porridge.

611
00:38:26,610 --> 00:38:29,310
Is this why you asked
what food is good for inflammation?

612
00:38:29,510 --> 00:38:31,880
Yes, you said mushrooms have
anti-inflammatory effects, Grandpa.

613
00:38:32,210 --> 00:38:34,620
- Here.
- Is that really you, Eun Bin?

614
00:38:35,050 --> 00:38:36,050
I know, right?

615
00:38:36,390 --> 00:38:40,520
Eun Bin, who used to torment Se Ri,
has changed so much.

616
00:38:41,460 --> 00:38:43,130
It's time I grew up.

617
00:38:43,130 --> 00:38:46,130
To be honest, I don't even remember
my birth mom anymore.

618
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:49,230
And she's the one who doted on me
and raised me all this time.

619
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:54,900
- You're after something.
- No, I'm not! I really mean it.

620
00:38:56,340 --> 00:38:57,470
Okay, I get it.

621
00:38:57,910 --> 00:39:02,010
Don't lift a finger. Just rest.
I'll even wash your face and teeth.

622
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:05,180
I'll be watching to see
how long this lasts.

623
00:39:05,250 --> 00:39:09,790
Go ahead and watch. In fact,
I'll call you Mom from now on.

624
00:39:10,050 --> 00:39:12,290
Here, Mom. Open wide.

625
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:23,770
Why is everyone staring at me
like that?

626
00:39:26,270 --> 00:39:27,370
Aunt, are you crying?

627
00:39:30,970 --> 00:39:33,710
Why are you crying?

628
00:39:34,740 --> 00:39:38,480
I guess I am.
Gosh, I'm being so silly. I'm sorry.

629
00:39:40,050 --> 00:39:41,080
No, don't be sorry.

630
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:43,090
Mom.

631
00:39:59,970 --> 00:40:02,100
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

632
00:40:02,710 --> 00:40:06,510
Honey, we need to eat too.
Here we go. Come on.

633
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:12,010
- Sweetie, let Mommy eat something.
- The meat's burning! What do we do?

634
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:13,350
Jeong Won, look at this.

635
00:40:17,750 --> 00:40:22,060
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

636
00:40:27,260 --> 00:40:30,030
Excuse me. Why do you have the baby?

637
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:34,570
The baby was being fussy,
so the parents couldn't eat.

638
00:40:35,300 --> 00:40:38,040
I wasn't busy,
so I offered to watch her.

639
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:43,080
- She doesn't seem fussy at all.
- I know, right?

640
00:40:43,550 --> 00:40:46,820
I'm a natural with babies.
I have four younger siblings.

641
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:48,120
Wow.

642
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:51,450
- I just have one older sister.
- I see.

643
00:40:52,490 --> 00:40:55,420
- You're a med student, right?
- I've graduated, actually.

644
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:57,360
I'm studying for my medical boards.

645
00:40:58,430 --> 00:40:59,630
How about you?

646
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:02,200
What's this "you" business?

647
00:41:02,530 --> 00:41:05,000
It's Min Seo.
You can call me Min Seo.

648
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,800
Right, sure.

649
00:41:08,070 --> 00:41:09,070
And what about you, Min Seo?

650
00:41:10,170 --> 00:41:13,810
I attend Johns Hopkins Med School,
and I'm from Baltimore.

651
00:41:14,110 --> 00:41:15,210
Baltimore?

652
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:18,450
Wait,
then what are you doing here now?

653
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:20,820
I'm on a leave of absence.

654
00:41:21,350 --> 00:41:22,590
I'm here to find someone.

655
00:41:23,450 --> 00:41:24,450
I see.

656
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,000
Mom?

657
00:41:35,970 --> 00:41:36,970
Hey.

658
00:41:38,700 --> 00:41:40,740
Why are you out here?
Is Ju Ah not home yet?

659
00:41:41,940 --> 00:41:43,110
Your sister's home.

660
00:41:45,270 --> 00:41:48,280
Then... Don't tell me
you were waiting for me.

661
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:52,650
Of course. I was worried someone
would snatch up my handsome son.

662
00:41:53,050 --> 00:41:55,520
Liar. You were just waiting
to nag me.

663
00:41:56,890 --> 00:42:00,720
All right,
I'll allow exactly three nags.

664
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:06,260
- Not nagging. They're questions.
- Nagging disguised as questions.

665
00:42:06,730 --> 00:42:07,730
Go on.

666
00:42:10,030 --> 00:42:11,270
Are you remembering
to take your medicine?

667
00:42:12,430 --> 00:42:14,840
Of course. Next, number two.

668
00:42:15,700 --> 00:42:17,540
Are you happy now that
you're working, not studying?

669
00:42:18,540 --> 00:42:19,540
I love it.

670
00:42:20,180 --> 00:42:22,240
It's a little tough, but...

671
00:42:22,810 --> 00:42:24,750
It's fun. I get to meet new people.

672
00:42:26,050 --> 00:42:27,050
Last one.

673
00:42:35,490 --> 00:42:37,490
What are you going to buy me
with your first paycheck?

674
00:42:41,730 --> 00:42:44,670
I'll buy you anything you want.

675
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:46,000
Really?

676
00:42:46,370 --> 00:42:48,470
- Really.
- I'm so excited!

677
00:42:49,340 --> 00:42:50,640
Let's go inside. It's cold.

678
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:52,040
Okay, let's go.

679
00:42:56,410 --> 00:42:58,250
When Eun Bin was little,

680
00:42:58,780 --> 00:43:00,920
whenever I'd go to her school
with an umbrella,

681
00:43:02,220 --> 00:43:04,490
she'd purposely yell out
in front of everyone,

682
00:43:04,990 --> 00:43:06,260
"Stepmom!"

683
00:43:07,490 --> 00:43:08,760
That's what she'd call me.

684
00:43:10,830 --> 00:43:14,430
But you know,
it never bothered me one bit.

685
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:18,500
Seeing her trying so hard
not to forget her birth mother...

686
00:43:19,170 --> 00:43:21,600
and trying not to get
attached to me...

687
00:43:24,010 --> 00:43:25,710
It just broke my heart.

688
00:43:28,780 --> 00:43:30,180
But after 16 years,

689
00:43:32,050 --> 00:43:33,650
she's finally calling me Mom.

690
00:43:36,120 --> 00:43:37,850
I don't think I can call you "Mom."

691
00:43:42,590 --> 00:43:43,690
It'd be weird.

692
00:43:46,100 --> 00:43:48,500
You look more like
an older sister than a mom.

693
00:43:50,370 --> 00:43:51,370
Honestly.

694
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:55,840
See? You smiled. I just said that
so you wouldn't keep crying.

695
00:43:57,070 --> 00:43:58,070
I see.

696
00:44:00,180 --> 00:44:03,210
So, I hope you're not disappointed
that I'm not marrying...

697
00:44:03,650 --> 00:44:05,210
into the Taehan Group family.

698
00:44:05,450 --> 00:44:08,120
Come on, I'm not that shallow.

699
00:44:08,550 --> 00:44:11,720
I was just happy to meet her,
thinking she was your girlfriend.

700
00:44:13,690 --> 00:44:17,990
So does that mean you'll approve
of anyone I love, no matter what?

701
00:44:18,230 --> 00:44:19,230
Of course.

702
00:44:19,960 --> 00:44:21,960
- You promise?
- Yes.

703
00:44:24,630 --> 00:44:25,630
Ms. Gong.

704
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:28,470
As long as it's not her.

705
00:44:31,870 --> 00:44:32,880
Gosh, that hurts.

706
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:35,180
Ouch, it hurts.

707
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:49,290
(Family Court)

708
00:44:49,390 --> 00:44:50,390
We'll see.

709
00:44:54,100 --> 00:44:55,130
Honey!

710
00:45:03,710 --> 00:45:05,610
Honey, have you been doing well?

711
00:45:06,510 --> 00:45:07,910
Don't call me that anymore.

712
00:45:08,210 --> 00:45:11,050
Come on. We aren't divorced yet,
so I can still call you "honey."

713
00:45:11,510 --> 00:45:12,510
You're still so...

714
00:45:13,080 --> 00:45:14,080
Pretty?

715
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:15,680
Shameless.

716
00:45:16,650 --> 00:45:19,660
You're still really mad at me,
aren't you?

717
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:22,960
Do you still miss me so much
it hurts?

718
00:45:23,590 --> 00:45:24,590
No.

719
00:45:26,200 --> 00:45:27,630
I don't think about you anymore.

720
00:45:28,230 --> 00:45:29,500
I haven't for a while now.

721
00:45:31,370 --> 00:45:34,000
Look at my sweet honey,
telling lies.

722
00:45:34,540 --> 00:45:37,940
Did I hurt you so much
that you changed?

723
00:45:38,670 --> 00:45:43,280
Don't be like that. Just forget me
and find someone nice, honey.

724
00:45:45,710 --> 00:45:46,720
Babe.

725
00:46:05,700 --> 00:46:07,300
Have you been waiting long, babe?

726
00:46:09,070 --> 00:46:10,070
"Babe?"

727
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:13,140
Yes, babe. Why?

728
00:46:13,540 --> 00:46:16,580
What... What is this?
Are you two dating?

729
00:46:16,910 --> 00:46:19,820
You... This is a blatant affair!

730
00:46:19,920 --> 00:46:21,780
An affair? Give me a break.

731
00:46:22,080 --> 00:46:24,090
If you haven't finalized
the divorce, it is an affair.

732
00:46:24,290 --> 00:46:26,890
Then go ahead and get divorced.
We're at the Family Court after all.

733
00:46:27,260 --> 00:46:29,730
- I have the papers right here.
- You... How could you...

734
00:46:30,230 --> 00:46:33,300
When did you two start dating?
Tell me it wasn't before us.

735
00:46:36,370 --> 00:46:38,000
You're really asking
for a punch, aren't you?

736
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:46,210
If you're seeing other guys,
I'm not giving up custody of Ji Hu.

737
00:46:47,340 --> 00:46:48,340
What?

738
00:46:48,780 --> 00:46:49,780
You.

739
00:46:50,450 --> 00:46:51,850
You said you didn't even want
your own kids,

740
00:46:53,580 --> 00:46:54,820
so why would you raise
someone else's?

741
00:46:56,590 --> 00:46:58,850
For the record,
I made it clear I don't want kids.

742
00:46:59,120 --> 00:47:00,120
What?

743
00:47:00,190 --> 00:47:02,890
If I hear one more word
about custody from this jerk,

744
00:47:04,290 --> 00:47:07,260
I'll take back the savings
and the deposit. All of it. Okay?

745
00:47:07,530 --> 00:47:10,370
- Come on, honey.
- Hey!

746
00:47:10,530 --> 00:47:11,630
(Family Court)

747
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:15,840
If you call my man "honey"
one more time,

748
00:47:16,310 --> 00:47:19,010
I will rip all of your hair out.

749
00:47:23,680 --> 00:47:26,780
You...
You'd better be good to Ji Hu.

750
00:47:26,850 --> 00:47:28,650
- Got it?
- Shut it!

751
00:47:28,920 --> 00:47:30,090
He's not even worth the anger.

752
00:47:31,350 --> 00:47:32,350
Let's go, babe.

753
00:47:34,390 --> 00:47:35,390
What the...

754
00:47:37,960 --> 00:47:38,960
What?

755
00:47:40,130 --> 00:47:41,130
Hey!

756
00:47:42,160 --> 00:47:46,570
Gosh, those two...
Wow, look at those cheaters!

757
00:47:47,100 --> 00:47:48,100
Unbelievable.

758
00:47:51,210 --> 00:47:54,440
The press reaction to the event
has been great,

759
00:47:54,540 --> 00:47:56,310
and on the online fashion pages,

760
00:47:56,310 --> 00:47:59,480
FG has broken into
the top ten search rankings.

761
00:48:00,250 --> 00:48:01,250
Oh, my.

762
00:48:01,550 --> 00:48:05,050
This has never happened
since I started. I'm overwhelmed.

763
00:48:06,090 --> 00:48:07,360
Have you seen the comments?

764
00:48:07,660 --> 00:48:10,790
People are going crazy asking
when Dr. Han's outfit comes out.

765
00:48:11,330 --> 00:48:12,530
And because of the charity campaign,

766
00:48:12,590 --> 00:48:14,700
our company's image
has gotten a huge boost too.

767
00:48:15,300 --> 00:48:18,670
Then our team will use
the feedback from the event...

768
00:48:18,730 --> 00:48:20,640
and start revising
the samples immediately.

769
00:48:21,240 --> 00:48:24,740
And Hyegyeong Department Store said
the event exceeded expectations,

770
00:48:24,740 --> 00:48:26,010
so they want to fast-track
the placement deal.

771
00:48:27,210 --> 00:48:29,680
Now, if we just get word
that we won the contest this week,

772
00:48:30,850 --> 00:48:32,010
everything would be perfect.

773
00:48:34,250 --> 00:48:37,550
Then should we try sending
good vibes out to the universe?

774
00:48:38,420 --> 00:48:39,420
Should we?

775
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:42,760
All right.

776
00:48:44,490 --> 00:48:46,600
Let's go!

777
00:48:46,760 --> 00:48:49,600
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

778
00:48:50,900 --> 00:48:52,700
Let's do this!

779
00:48:54,840 --> 00:48:57,740
- Let's head in, Director.
- Okay.

780
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:04,650
I'm so relieved
the results were good.

781
00:49:05,110 --> 00:49:07,350
It's too early to celebrate.
This is just the beginning.

782
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:10,920
You have to go straight
to the marketing meeting, right?

783
00:49:12,050 --> 00:49:15,320
Yes. I'll be late tonight,
so head home without me.

784
00:49:15,820 --> 00:49:19,900
Gosh, we share an office,
but we barely get to see each other.

785
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:22,500
That's why I said we should've gone
on a date yesterday.

786
00:49:23,000 --> 00:49:25,700
And make sure you take that
when you leave.

787
00:49:26,700 --> 00:49:29,570
It's a neck pillow and some
anti-inflammatory quince-ginger tea.

788
00:49:30,010 --> 00:49:31,810
Give them to your stepmom for me.

789
00:49:32,140 --> 00:49:34,040
So this is why you couldn't see me?
You were out buying all this?

790
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:35,280
Yes.

791
00:49:35,610 --> 00:49:38,680
And my grandma also packed
pain relief patches and vitamins,

792
00:49:38,780 --> 00:49:39,780
so make sure you give those to her.

793
00:49:40,650 --> 00:49:43,050
Got it.
My stepmom is going to love this.

794
00:49:43,390 --> 00:49:45,090
- Really?
- Yes.

795
00:49:50,190 --> 00:49:53,860
Come on. I told you not to eat
late-night snacks after closing.

796
00:49:53,930 --> 00:49:57,600
A stomach bug again. Keep this up,
and you'll wreck your stomach.

797
00:49:57,670 --> 00:49:59,130
Honestly, this is so upsetting.

798
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:01,340
I can just have some porridge,
right?

799
00:50:01,600 --> 00:50:04,840
Take your medicine on time.
I'll call at every meal to check.

800
00:50:04,970 --> 00:50:06,240
Okay, I will.

801
00:50:08,340 --> 00:50:13,220
Your picture in that article
came out great, Doctor.

802
00:50:14,120 --> 00:50:16,350
- You saw it?
- Saw it? I did more than that.

803
00:50:16,820 --> 00:50:20,620
I've been bragging about you
all over the market.

804
00:50:21,990 --> 00:50:24,460
You and Dr. Han...

805
00:50:24,660 --> 00:50:27,700
are the pride of Onjeong Market.

806
00:50:28,330 --> 00:50:31,630
You're making me blush. But I guess
everyone recognizes talent, right?

807
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:33,400
Yes, of course.

808
00:50:34,370 --> 00:50:36,840
(Han Seong Mi and Gong Jeong Han
attend FG's One-Point Lesson)

809
00:50:36,910 --> 00:50:38,670
Look at him, enjoying himself.
Darn it.

810
00:50:39,140 --> 00:50:41,280
After the humiliation
he put us through.

811
00:50:50,620 --> 00:50:54,190
Yes, it's a huge relief
this didn't end up in an article.

812
00:50:55,090 --> 00:50:56,830
My poor Se Ri was almost humiliated.

813
00:51:00,430 --> 00:51:03,370
Hello! The "Human Theater" producer!
To what do I owe the pleasure?

814
00:51:03,700 --> 00:51:06,870
I was planning on stopping by today
to scout locations and the market...

815
00:51:07,270 --> 00:51:08,640
and was wondering if you'd be free.

816
00:51:09,070 --> 00:51:11,710
I see! Yes, of course.
Please, come on by.

817
00:51:11,910 --> 00:51:14,410
You're welcome anytime.
Yes, I'll be waiting for you. Okay.

818
00:51:25,550 --> 00:51:27,560
(Family Court)

819
00:51:46,740 --> 00:51:47,880
You look pretty today.

820
00:51:52,150 --> 00:51:53,250
I put in a little extra effort.

821
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:56,180
You're not just going to go home
dressed like that, are you?

822
00:51:57,120 --> 00:51:58,120
I am.

823
00:51:58,850 --> 00:52:00,120
Where else would I go?

824
00:52:10,530 --> 00:52:11,530
Hang out with me.

825
00:52:14,540 --> 00:52:15,540
To celebrate our divorce.

826
00:52:17,610 --> 00:52:18,610
Deal.

827
00:52:22,410 --> 00:52:24,910
Here we go.

828
00:52:26,380 --> 00:52:29,720
- The rabbit! That one!
- Okay, I'm going.

829
00:52:29,920 --> 00:52:31,220
Come on, grab it.

830
00:52:32,620 --> 00:52:34,260
Yes! Come on!

831
00:52:35,060 --> 00:52:36,060
You got it!

832
00:52:44,070 --> 00:52:47,370
Clank. Here it comes! Shoot!

833
00:52:47,370 --> 00:52:48,370
Shoot!

834
00:52:51,270 --> 00:52:52,840
Rat-a-tat-tat. They're coming!

835
00:52:56,340 --> 00:53:00,350
Remember how we'd always go
to the arcade after final exams?

836
00:53:01,420 --> 00:53:02,880
The one in Heungseong Plaza...

837
00:53:03,820 --> 00:53:05,050
- Galaxy Arcade.
- Galaxy Arcade.

838
00:53:16,570 --> 00:53:17,570
Are you okay?

839
00:53:20,270 --> 00:53:21,270
It's a beautiful day.

840
00:53:28,840 --> 00:53:32,480
Hey, Nurse Oh!
All quiet on our patrol.

841
00:53:32,550 --> 00:53:34,450
Abnormality detected
while heading home.

842
00:53:34,720 --> 00:53:35,720
You scared me.

843
00:53:35,720 --> 00:53:37,020
You must be out of your meds.

844
00:53:37,120 --> 00:53:38,350
Why didn't you come in
for your checkup?

845
00:53:38,590 --> 00:53:40,560
Oh, I'm all better now.

846
00:53:41,220 --> 00:53:43,020
All better? What are you
talking about? Look at this.

847
00:53:43,090 --> 00:53:45,590
You've always got the sniffles.
Goodness.

848
00:53:46,390 --> 00:53:47,500
What? What are you doing?

849
00:53:47,800 --> 00:53:50,670
I guess I can handle the patrol
from here on my own.

850
00:53:50,730 --> 00:53:54,000
Wait, Chief! What? Hey.

851
00:53:54,370 --> 00:53:55,470
Hey, what do you think you're doing?

852
00:53:55,770 --> 00:53:59,440
Let me check your runny nose.
I need to see if it's thick or thin.

853
00:53:59,440 --> 00:54:00,540
Come on!

854
00:54:00,980 --> 00:54:04,110
Do you always have to be so rough?
You even yanked my pants down.

855
00:54:04,210 --> 00:54:07,880
- Why stare at my snot?
- Give me a break.

856
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:11,720
Here.

857
00:54:13,050 --> 00:54:16,630
Stop it. You're not better,
so come to the clinic tomorrow.

858
00:54:17,030 --> 00:54:18,190
If you don't, I swear...

859
00:54:18,730 --> 00:54:19,730
I'll come and get you myself.

860
00:54:20,660 --> 00:54:21,660
My goodness.

861
00:54:21,960 --> 00:54:24,300
If you're going to hunt me down,
why not do it in the daytime?

862
00:54:26,070 --> 00:54:30,340
- Were you waiting for me?
- What? No, not really.

863
00:54:31,440 --> 00:54:32,440
Were you busy?

864
00:54:32,770 --> 00:54:35,980
Yes. Mr. Gong was at the courthouse
for his divorce.

865
00:54:36,610 --> 00:54:37,610
I see.

866
00:54:38,180 --> 00:54:41,920
Oh, boy. After the terrible ordeal
he's been through,

867
00:54:42,220 --> 00:54:44,190
I doubt he'll ever be able
to date anyone again.

868
00:54:45,650 --> 00:54:48,190
I wouldn't worry about that.

869
00:54:48,720 --> 00:54:49,720
Why not?

870
00:54:50,030 --> 00:54:51,930
- Chief, wait up.
- Why?

871
00:54:51,990 --> 00:54:53,060
- Hey!
- Why are you following me?

872
00:54:54,230 --> 00:54:55,230
Here.

873
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:01,540
Stop peeling and eat some yourself.

874
00:55:02,600 --> 00:55:04,070
I actually like peeling them.

875
00:55:05,810 --> 00:55:07,980
Who actually enjoys
such a tedious task?

876
00:55:08,910 --> 00:55:10,250
What do you mean? I like it.

877
00:55:10,810 --> 00:55:14,580
I'd rather see my niece
and nephew eat than eat myself.

878
00:55:16,520 --> 00:55:19,620
If you're like this with them,
I can't imagine you with your own.

879
00:55:22,390 --> 00:55:25,290
Tell me about it.
I'm a total pro at raising kids.

880
00:55:26,760 --> 00:55:28,000
That ship has sailed now.

881
00:55:32,330 --> 00:55:34,940
This is the first time
anyone's ever peeled shrimp for me.

882
00:55:35,700 --> 00:55:40,440
- Really?
- Yes. Everyone spoiled my brother,

883
00:55:40,510 --> 00:55:42,040
so I was always left out
in the cold.

884
00:55:42,780 --> 00:55:45,880
And as for Ji Hu's Dad,
he only ever looked out for himself.

885
00:55:50,220 --> 00:55:52,490
- Can we get more shrimp over here?
- Right away.

886
00:55:52,550 --> 00:55:53,560
Just a second.

887
00:55:55,420 --> 00:55:56,790
Let me get the bones out
of this fish for you, too.

888
00:56:06,000 --> 00:56:07,540
That woman must have been
a real fool.

889
00:56:07,840 --> 00:56:10,710
Leaving a man like you...
What's so great about Ji Hu's Dad?

890
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:14,110
The same goes for your husband then.

891
00:56:14,680 --> 00:56:16,710
Here, try it.
I got all the bones out.

892
00:56:22,380 --> 00:56:24,920
Thanks for asking me
to hang out today.

893
00:56:26,220 --> 00:56:27,520
I thought today would be
the most miserable...

894
00:56:28,690 --> 00:56:30,790
and saddest day.

895
00:56:36,060 --> 00:56:37,070
Me too.

896
00:56:50,380 --> 00:56:52,150
I said I'm walking you home.

897
00:56:52,450 --> 00:56:55,520
That's okay.
What if someone sees us?

898
00:56:58,590 --> 00:57:02,120
You're right. Both our families
would flip if they saw us, right?

899
00:57:02,520 --> 00:57:03,560
Of course, they would.

900
00:57:06,630 --> 00:57:09,060
Dong Suk,
how's your new sister-in-law?

901
00:57:09,260 --> 00:57:10,270
Is she doing okay?

902
00:57:10,870 --> 00:57:12,530
Yes, she's totally fine.

903
00:57:14,970 --> 00:57:16,040
Your feet are hurting, aren't they?

904
00:57:16,240 --> 00:57:19,140
Yes, it's from wearing these heels.
It's been a while.

905
00:57:23,910 --> 00:57:26,280
Give me your foot.
I'll give it a rub.

906
00:57:27,680 --> 00:57:29,020
You know it's my specialty.

907
00:57:30,050 --> 00:57:32,620
- No, it's okay.
- What do you mean, "it's okay?"

908
00:57:33,250 --> 00:57:35,220
Think of it as physical therapy.
Now, give it here.

909
00:57:36,260 --> 00:57:38,560
Stop, you're embarrassing me.

910
00:57:38,690 --> 00:57:41,460
- What's so embarrassing? Come here.
- Stop it.

911
00:57:41,530 --> 00:57:43,330
- But your foot hurts. Come on.
- No!

912
00:57:43,400 --> 00:57:45,470
- Just let me... Come on!
- I said, stop! I'm okay, really!

913
00:57:48,040 --> 00:57:49,140
Are you okay?

914
00:57:52,110 --> 00:57:53,110
Dong Suk.

915
00:57:53,610 --> 00:57:55,010
Next time,
instead of using your feet,

916
00:57:55,510 --> 00:57:56,580
let's use our words.

917
00:58:00,050 --> 00:58:01,080
I'm sorry.

918
00:58:03,450 --> 00:58:05,650
- Hey.
- Oh, no. I dropped my rabbit.

919
00:58:13,800 --> 00:58:14,900
Dad.

920
00:58:15,930 --> 00:58:18,400
What brings you upstairs?

921
00:58:19,300 --> 00:58:20,370
Did it go okay?

922
00:58:23,070 --> 00:58:24,070
I'm sorry.

923
00:58:25,070 --> 00:58:26,370
I ended up getting a divorce, too.

924
00:58:29,540 --> 00:58:32,550
Your brother met someone new
and is living a good life now.

925
00:58:33,920 --> 00:58:35,050
You can do the same.

926
00:58:37,320 --> 00:58:38,550
Me? How could I?

927
00:58:41,360 --> 00:58:42,960
Don't you worry about Ji Hu.

928
00:58:45,660 --> 00:58:46,900
I'll take care of him.

929
00:59:05,250 --> 00:59:06,680
So, how are you feeling?

930
00:59:08,320 --> 00:59:09,350
Were you upset to see her?

931
00:59:10,420 --> 00:59:12,220
No, not at all.

932
00:59:13,790 --> 00:59:17,730
Good. When one door closes,
another one opens.

933
00:59:18,760 --> 00:59:20,360
But you're home earlier
than I expected.

934
00:59:20,700 --> 00:59:21,700
Why?

935
00:59:22,460 --> 00:59:24,530
Did you think I'd be out drinking
and feeling sorry for myself?

936
00:59:24,770 --> 00:59:26,730
Yes.
You weren't answering your phone.

937
00:59:27,570 --> 00:59:28,770
I guess I didn't check my phone.

938
00:59:31,010 --> 00:59:32,440
You called me.

939
00:59:36,110 --> 00:59:37,810
I got a text from the hospital
I interviewed with.

940
00:59:38,110 --> 00:59:39,750
- Really? What does it say?
- Yes.

941
00:59:40,650 --> 00:59:42,050
This is
Pureun Rehabilitation Hospital.

942
00:59:42,650 --> 00:59:46,090
We are pleased to offer you
the Physical Therapist position.

943
00:59:46,990 --> 00:59:47,990
Well?

944
00:59:49,060 --> 00:59:50,160
I didn't get it.

945
00:59:51,060 --> 00:59:52,060
You didn't?

946
00:59:52,590 --> 00:59:55,200
I guess you'll have to
look for something else.

947
00:59:55,700 --> 00:59:56,700
Mom.

948
00:59:57,700 --> 00:59:59,370
I just want to keep working
at our clinic.

949
01:00:02,340 --> 01:00:03,540
Are you sure
you'll be okay with that?

950
01:00:03,810 --> 01:00:05,370
Yes, I'm sure.

951
01:00:06,870 --> 01:00:08,180
I've realized I want to stay here.

952
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:18,050
Did you get home okay?

953
01:00:18,450 --> 01:00:19,550
Have you eaten?

954
01:00:20,390 --> 01:00:21,890
Hey, I asked you first.

955
01:00:22,990 --> 01:00:24,390
I said, have you eaten?

956
01:00:24,860 --> 01:00:26,130
No, I haven't.

957
01:00:26,590 --> 01:00:29,700
Why do you keep asking?
Did you leave food at my door again?

958
01:00:30,730 --> 01:00:31,830
Ta-da!

959
01:00:33,200 --> 01:00:35,140
What are you doing here?

960
01:00:36,640 --> 01:00:40,040
I thought we'd eat something good
and watch a horror movie.

961
01:00:40,340 --> 01:00:42,140
You remembered I like horror movies.

962
01:00:42,340 --> 01:00:46,080
Of course. We saw
"The Silence of the Horses."

963
01:00:46,580 --> 01:00:49,080
- Shall we watch it again tonight?
- Sure!

964
01:00:49,520 --> 01:00:52,450
You should've asked for the code
and waited inside.

965
01:00:53,620 --> 01:00:55,820
Then it wouldn't be a surprise.

966
01:00:57,360 --> 01:00:58,360
Let's go inside.

967
01:01:00,230 --> 01:01:03,400
Why did the "Human Theater" producer
show up out of the blue?

968
01:01:04,600 --> 01:01:07,170
He said he wanted to look around
the market before the shoot.

969
01:01:07,740 --> 01:01:11,240
He wanted to see Jeong Han too,
so I made an excuse about a meeting.

970
01:01:11,410 --> 01:01:13,170
I was late because I had to
treat him to a meal and see him off.

971
01:01:14,580 --> 01:01:15,880
Honey, what are we going to do?

972
01:01:16,410 --> 01:01:19,010
Councilor Hwang's people
contacted me.

973
01:01:19,850 --> 01:01:20,920
What? What about?

974
01:01:21,580 --> 01:01:25,050
He asked if he could also make
an appearance on "Human Theater."

975
01:01:25,620 --> 01:01:26,620
Really?

976
01:01:27,790 --> 01:01:30,990
He wants to appear natural,
like you two are old friends,

977
01:01:31,130 --> 01:01:34,630
so he wants to get closer
to you before then.

978
01:01:34,960 --> 01:01:37,330
What? And?

979
01:01:37,400 --> 01:01:40,640
I tentatively scheduled a meeting
for next week, but...

980
01:01:40,970 --> 01:01:42,040
What should we do?

981
01:01:42,470 --> 01:01:44,140
This is driving me crazy.

982
01:01:45,070 --> 01:01:46,270
That jerk, Gong Jeong Han.

983
01:01:46,840 --> 01:01:49,140
Seriously, isn't there anything
we can do?

984
01:01:50,040 --> 01:01:51,750
I've thought about it all day too,
but...

985
01:01:51,850 --> 01:01:54,920
Maybe it's because of my fall,
but my brain just isn't working.

986
01:01:56,750 --> 01:01:57,790
Oh, boy.

987
01:01:59,220 --> 01:02:01,890
If only you'd actually gotten hurt
when you fell,

988
01:02:02,520 --> 01:02:05,130
we could've used that to blackmail
that jerk Gong Jeong Han.

989
01:02:06,860 --> 01:02:07,860
What?

990
01:02:08,830 --> 01:02:11,430
I... What am I even saying?

991
01:02:12,070 --> 01:02:14,970
I wasn't in my right mind.
I'm so sorry, honey.

992
01:02:15,370 --> 01:02:17,510
I'm just so desperate,
I didn't know what I was saying.

993
01:02:18,040 --> 01:02:19,640
Oh, my.

994
01:02:20,310 --> 01:02:21,310
Honey...

995
01:02:22,140 --> 01:02:23,580
You're a genius, aren't you?

996
01:02:24,210 --> 01:02:26,810
- That's a brilliant idea.
- What?

997
01:02:27,220 --> 01:02:28,220
You think so?

998
01:02:30,120 --> 01:02:32,120
But come on,
everyone knows you're okay.

999
01:02:32,720 --> 01:02:34,720
How are you going to pretend
you're badly hurt?

1000
01:02:36,160 --> 01:02:38,630
That's true. What should we do?

1001
01:02:39,830 --> 01:02:42,230
If only we had a video of the fall.

1002
01:02:45,530 --> 01:02:46,530
A video?

1003
01:03:08,790 --> 01:03:10,420
What's wrong? What's going on?

1004
01:03:18,200 --> 01:03:19,930
What do you mean a video was posted?

1005
01:03:20,970 --> 01:03:22,440
I thought we had it all taken down.

1006
01:03:23,570 --> 01:03:27,240
It seems someone posted a copy
early this morning, of all times.

1007
01:03:28,180 --> 01:03:30,110
To make matters worse,
a YouTuber sensationalized it...

1008
01:03:30,110 --> 01:03:31,450
and posted their own version.

1009
01:03:32,310 --> 01:03:33,610
How many views?

1010
01:03:36,580 --> 01:03:37,590
Five thousand?

1011
01:03:39,520 --> 01:03:40,560
Fifty thousand.

1012
01:03:42,560 --> 01:03:43,690
(Taehan Group)

1013
01:03:44,730 --> 01:03:47,330
So, what's in the video?

1014
01:03:58,740 --> 01:04:01,280
(Gong Ju Ah,
Head Designer at Taehan Group)

1015
01:04:04,410 --> 01:04:06,280
(Taehan Group Designer Shoves
and Injures VIP Client)

1016
01:04:06,350 --> 01:04:08,120
(Accident or Intentional?)

1017
01:04:08,720 --> 01:04:09,720
Unbelievable.

1018
01:04:12,190 --> 01:04:13,190
But...

1019
01:04:13,750 --> 01:04:14,990
Who on earth would do that?

1020
01:04:16,090 --> 01:04:18,660
Who posted it isn't
what's important right now.

1021
01:04:19,760 --> 01:04:21,300
Corporate HR...

1022
01:04:22,000 --> 01:04:24,070
is convening a disciplinary hearing.

1023
01:04:25,400 --> 01:04:26,470
A disciplinary hearing?

1024
01:04:55,360 --> 01:04:58,370
(Recipe For Love)

1025
01:04:59,530 --> 01:05:00,970
- Are you seeing Mr. Gong?
- Hey, here...

1026
01:05:01,670 --> 01:05:02,700
You can't date him.

1027
01:05:04,110 --> 01:05:06,340
Who were you drinking with
to get like this?

1028
01:05:07,740 --> 01:05:11,180
By myself. I was so upset.
I just had one drink.

1029
01:05:11,580 --> 01:05:12,980
- I had a fight.
- With who?

1030
01:05:12,980 --> 01:05:16,180
Hey, Dong Suk!
The woman with the fragrant shampoo.

1031
01:05:16,180 --> 01:05:18,490
It's so nonsensical.
Doesn't it feel intentional?

1032
01:05:18,490 --> 01:05:20,920
I never should have invited
Pacu Nacho's parents.

1033
01:05:21,320 --> 01:05:23,860
- I'm so sorry.
- Should we tell Hyun Bin the truth?

1034
01:05:24,090 --> 01:05:26,490
At this point, we have no choice
but to see it through.

1035
01:05:26,560 --> 01:05:29,260
I'm trying to find
who first leaked the video.
